text: Ivy Vila Wittingham (born 22 July 2001) is a Cuban female volleyball player. She is a member of the Cuba women's national volleyball team and played for Camagüey in 2018. She was part of the Cuban national team at the 2018 FIVB Volleyball Women's World Championship, and 2019 FIVB Volleyball Women's U20 World Championship. == References == ==Other websites == * Player - IVY MAY VILA WITTINGHAM - FIVB Volleyball Women's World Championship Japan 2018 * Ivy Vila Wittingham - Volleyball player profile & career statistics - Global Sports Archive * Camagüey´s athletes lead the Cuba in Panamericano under-20 volleyball * Cuba won its first gold medal www.norceca.info * Cuba Won the Pan American U-20 Cup against Dominican Republic www.artemisaradioweb.icrt.cu Category:2001 births Category:Living people Category:Cuban volleyball players
